						<summary>

						<p>This is dated in Śaka 1206, Tāraṇa, Tai, Saṅkrama and records the gift of the <hi rend="italic">magamai</hi> duties on articles of merchandise levied at Guṇḍalūr and the śōtram(rent?) from the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna, Piḍāri-paṟṟu, Bhairava-sthāna</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Gaṇapati-sthāna</hi> lands at the place, for burning perpetual lamps and for offerings and worship to the god in the temple of Tiruvagastīśvaram-uḍaiya Nāyaṉar, for the merit of Śōmidēva-Mahārāja. The identity of this chief is not clear. </p>						

						</summary>
